      "## Why it works on you (and it does work)",
      "Scent is wired more directly to memory and emotion than any of your other senses. The pathway that processes smell sits right next to the parts of the brain that handle emotion and memory formation, which is why a single whiff can drop you into a specific moment from years ago faster than a photograph can. Retailers exploit this in two honest ways.",
