      "So concentrate your remaining minutes there. A quick pass in the entry — shoes away, a clear console, a wiped surface — plus a tidy living room with cushions straightened and any lingering cup taken to the kitchen does more for the *feel* of the room than scenting a guest bedroom no one will enter. Get these two right and the house reads as cared for. For a deeper room-by-room approach when you have more time, our guides on [how to make your house smell good](/blog/how-to-make-your-house-smell-good) and [how to make your living room smell good](/blog/how-to-make-your-living-room-smell-good) build on exactly this logic.",
      "## Minutes 20–30: Set a Settled, Welcoming Scent",
